Althought restricted to forward propagation of the field, the above equation is still exact in that no paraxiality approximation has been made. In order to evaluate the radical in equation (6), one approach would be to use a Taylor expansion. The first order of the expansion leads to the standard, paraxial BPM, while higher orders lead to more accurate representations. However expansion via Padé approximations69 is more accurate than Taylor expansion for the same order of terms. This approach leads to the following wide-angle equation:8∂U∂z=ikrNm(P)Dn(P)U\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
